The article announces several nominations and appointments made by the United States government. Some of the notable nominations include Jerome M. Adams to be the Surgeon General of the Public Health Service, Luis E. Arreaga to be the Ambassador to the Republic of Guatemala, and Brenda Burman to be the Commissioner of Reclamation. Other nominations include Christopher Campbell, Peter B. Davidson, Joshua A. Deahl, Janet Dhillon, Douglas W. Domenech, Matthew P. Donovan, Eric S. Dreiband, William J. Emanuel, Gerald W. Fauth, Susan M. Gordon, Jason Kearns, Ellen M. Lord, Robert L. Sumwalt III, and Krishna R. Urs.